      "content": "That \"authentication failed\" message usually means the router isn't getting a valid signal from your ISP line, so it's not necessarily a hardware fault inside the router itself. It could be a loose line, a bad modem, or a temporary glitch in the ISP's network. Before assuming the router is broken, try resetting the router to factory defaults (hold the reset button for 10 seconds), then reconfigure the ISP credentials in the admin panel. If the red light persists after a reset, it is likely an external line issue rather than an internal hardware failure.",
